Boil a full kettle.

Meanwhile, cut the @Tenderstem® Broccoli{80%grams} into thirds.

Pour the boiled water into a #saucepan{} with 1/2 tsp @salt{} on high heat.

Boil the @Spinach and Ricotta Ravioli{250%grams} and broccoli, ~{3%mins}.

Once cooked, drain and pop back into the pan. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in another saucepan on medium-high heat.

Once hot, stir in the @Tomato Puree{30%grams}, @Creme Fraiche{75%grams}, @Vegetable Stock Paste{10%grams} and @Water{75%milliliters}.

Bring to a boil, then simmer, ~{1-2%mins}.

Add the @Baby Spinach{40%grams} in handfuls, making sure it's piping hot, ~{1-2%mins}.

Next, add the @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{20%grams}, pasta and broccoli to the sauce.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Stir, ~{1%min}.

Share your creamy tomato ravioli between your #bowls{}.

Enjoy!